  "text": "Dietary intake of n-3 and n-6 PUFAs is important also for bone metabolism. The long-term effect of n-3 and n-6 PUFAs supplementation in a mouse model of rheumatoid arthritis (MRL/lpr female mouse) was evaluated on bone mineral density (BMD) and metabolism. In this model, fish oil supplementation leads to a higher BMD and to a lesser extent synovial inflammation than corn oil supplementation. Furthermore, fish oil intake decreased RANKL and increased osteoprotegerin gene expression [CITATION_1] .",
